# Installation

Kathe is built around three*) components:

- `kathe.py` - a script to create datasets
- `app.py` - a GUI to analyse the dataset based via a webgui/API
- `flushcache.py` - a supporting script to manage Kathe's redis caches

*) This setup, or at least the regular workflow, will change when we add storing of info to the API.

## Install using Docker

Currently, Kathe can be quickly deployed using Docker and Docker-compose. To do use, make sure your system is running Docker and has an internet connection for pulling images. You can then build and run Kathe locally as follows:

1)  ```git clone https://github.com/avuko/kathe.git ```

2)  ```cd [kathe] && docker build . -t kathe:latest ```

3)  Verify the image is built using: ```docker image ls``` 

4)  Start the web application using ```docker-compose up -d ```

To access the GUI, navigate to https://localhost:8000 

## Manual local install 

If you want to avoid using Docker, you can also run the application as a stand-alone python3 app.

Requirements:
*   Python 3.6 or higher
*   Redis running on localhost:6379
*   Pip and pipenv

1)  ```git clone https://github.com/avuko/kathe.git ```

2) ```cd [kathe] && pipenv install ```

3) ```pipenv shell ```

4) ```cd ./web && python app.py ```

To access the GUI, navigate to https://localhost:8000 

## Available routes

Currently the following routes are available. In the future, more routes will become available to perform various operations regarding the processing and retrieval of new information.

```GET /```
Displays some introductory information on Katherine Johnson.

```GET /kathe/```
```GET /kathe/?search=query```
Displays the main application GUI. This GUI is used to search through the underlying database and view information nodes and the links between them.

![Hello World](data:image/png;base64,)

```GET /search/```
```GET /search/?search=query```
Returns JSON-formatted information on nodes and/or links related to a search query. Search queries should be either a SHA256 hash, an ssdeep hash or a text string containing the context you want to search for.

```GET /info/```
```GET /info/?search=query```
Returns JSON-formatted information on a specific ssdeep-hash. 

```POST /add/```
Upload new JSON-formatted content. An example request will be available here soon. `TODO` 
## Filling the database

I'm using `malpedia.py` to load malpedia information into the dataset. I've received a very large set of meta-info from Hybrid Analysis, so that is loaded as well using `kathe.py`'s csv function.

## Cleaning the cache

`flushcache.py` is a quick and dirty tool to delete all the cached sets etc. from the db. Further optimization would be to auto-delete all caches with other than current timestamps. This is a `TODO`.
